    "guide_chunks": {
      "watford_18": {
        "chunk_id": "watford_18",
        "source": "Wikivoyage:Watford",
        "text": "Cafés - Presence coffee shop with paninis, muffins, with a spa upstairs and a gift shop out front. TJ Hughes has a restaurant/café. For the more traditional fry-up, head to Aroma at the bottom of the high street for relatively healthy and delicious breakfasts, chips, burgers etc. Toast, next to Roosters and almost opposite the Palace Theatre, serves sandwiches, juice etc. Try Go Kula cafe on Market Place for vegetarian food but it is a bit hit and miss. Best to go there for a chat, read a few books and meet the local mums and toddlers. The YMCA serves good food - it is behind Poundland/next to the indoor market.\n\nCoffee - Starbucks and Costa in the Harlequin, Caffe Nero by St. Mary's Church on the High Street, Presence in the north end of the High Street, McDonald's on either end of the High Street. Plenty of places with plenty of choices.\n\nDrink",
        "score": 0.10342575343696414
      },
      "watford_17": {
        "chunk_id": "watford_17",
        "source": "Wikivoyage:Watford",
        "text": "Fast food - Two McDonalds (with an extra 2 in the north of the town), Five Guys, two Subways, various pizza takeaway places (Dominos, Pizza Hut, Pizza Express and various kebab shops. Roosters Peri Peri Chicken is halal and serves very inexpensive but absolutely delicious chicken meals, including wraps, burgers, etc., and even apple pies and ice cream in the summer. Try the chicken burger meal. Yum. For a sit-down, go to Pepe's, opposite the indoor market (behind Poundland) which serves Greek Cypriot fare as well as burgers, steaks, sandwiches, and puddings.\n\nVegetarian - GoKula Vegetarian Cafe, a vegetarian and vegan fast food restaurant with links to the nearby Hari Krishna Temple. A breakfast & brunch restaurant but not evenings. At 65 Market Street.\n\nHalal - Roosters (burgers, chicken wings, chips...), various kebab shops.",
        "score": 0.092124555770946
      },
      "watford_6": {
        "chunk_id": "watford_6",
        "source": "Wikivoyage:Watford",
        "text": "Caledonian Sleeper – Daily overnight sleeper train to and from Glasgow Central and Edinburgh.\n \n Daytime London Northwestern Railway services from St Albans Abbey, Park Street, How Wood, Bricket Wood and Watford Junction call at 51.687 -0.382 2 Garston and 51.676 -0.39 3 Watford North in the northern part of the town. Trains run roughly once per hour. Oyster and contactless cards cannot be used for travel to or from these stations.",
        "score": 0.06775215181968697
      }
    },
